$ cmd.exe batch files: remove extension of a file name

In a → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/batch-files[cmd.exe batch file], the → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/variables/tilde[«tilde positional modifier»] `dpn` can be used to remove the → development/filename-extensions[filename extension]
(that was passed to the script via a → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/batch-files/arguments[script-argument]):

gh|about-cmd.exe|/variables/tilde/remove-extension.bat||

Execution of the script:
code {
C:\path\to\script> remove-extension.bat %temp%\foo.bat
filename:                   C:\Users\Rene\AppData\Local\Temp\foo.bat
filename without extension: C:\Users\Rene\AppData\Local\Temp\foo
code }

sa:
  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/variables/tilde
